Oxalic acid was also efficient for lixiviation of calcined LFP, as demonstrated by Li et al. in 2018
[207]. During this process, illustrated in Figure 16, the calcined LFP was exposed to 0.3 M oxalic acid

oxide. The iron-rich residue was recovered through filtration and Li was separated from the
phosphate solution using an ionic sieve.
